  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">A solution of the Schrödinger equation written in terms of hyperspherical Jacobi coordinates is presented. The wave function and the potential are projected onto the space of a single reference pair Jacobi coordinate. The ground state binding energies and sizes obtained with the formalism, for an even number of bosons up to <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math> , and for the 6 Li, 12 C, 16 O and 40 Ca nuclei, are compared to the results in the literature.</subfield>
